'''[[San Marino]]''' participated in the '''[[Eurovision Song Contest 2012]]''' in [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], selecting their entry through an internal selection, organised by the Sanmarinese broadcaster [[San Marino RTV]] (SMRTV).

==Internal selection==
===Artist===
SMRTV confirmed on 14 March, that [[Valentina Monetta]] would represent San Marino in the Eurovision Song Contest 2012 in May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smtvsanmarino.sm/default.asp?id=623|title=Valentina Monetta rappresenter<U+00E0> San Marino a Baku 2012|language=Italian|work=[[San Marino RTV]]|accessdate=14 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=48973&_t=valentina_monetta_to_represent_san_marino|title=Valentina Monetta to represent San Marino|last=Roxburgh|first=Gordon|work=[[European Broadcasting Union|EBU]]|accessdate=14 March 2012}}</ref>

===Song===
On 16 March 2012, in a special programme by SMRTV with Valentina Monetta, "[[Facebook Uh, Oh, Oh]]" was presented as the Sanmarinese entry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=49183&_t=valentina_monetta_to_sing_facebook_uhohoh|title=Valentina Monetta to sing "Facebook Uh,Oh,Oh"|last=Roxburgh|first=Gordon|date=16 March 2012|work=[[European Broadcasting Union|EBU]]|accessdate=18 March 2012}}</ref>

====Disqualification====
However, it was announced that the songs lyrics breached rule 1.2.2. (g), which states; 
{{quote|"The lyrics and/or performance of the songs shall not bring the Shows, the ESC as such or the EBU into disrepute. No lyrics, speeches, gestures of a political or similar nature shall be permitted during the ESC. No swearing or other unacceptable language shall be allowed in the lyrics or in the performances of the songs. ''No commercial messages of any kind shall be allowed''. A breach of this rule may result in disqualification."}}
EBU ordered San Marino to either change the lyrics and the title of the song or select a new song, no later than 23 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=49493&_t=ebu_san_marino_song_lyrics_in_breach_of_rules|title=EBU: San Marino song lyrics in breach of Rules|last=Siim|first=Jarmo|work=[[European Broadcasting Union|EBU]]|accessdate=18 March 2012}}</ref>

A revised version of the song, under the title "The Social Network Song" was presented on 22 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=49823&_t=the_social_network_song_for_san_marino|title='The Social Network song' for San Marino|work=[[European Broadcasting Union|EBU]]|accessdate=22 March 2012}}</ref>

==At Eurovision==
San Marino competed in the second half of the first semi-final on 22 May, but did not proceed to the final. After the grand final on the 26th of May, full results have shown that the song ended on 14th place with 31 points, making the entry San Marino's best placing in Eurovision compared to previous years and has shown that there were improvements.<ref>http://www.eurovision.tv/page/history/by-year/contest?event=1573#Scoreboard</ref>


